# Consult: Interior/NPC black — specular `pow()` NaN

## Root cause (confirmed, with one refinement)

**Confirmed:** The black interior pixel is **`o0 = NaN` born in the per-pixel specular `pow()`**, lowered by `fxc` to `exp2(materialSpecularPower * log2(saturate(dot(H,N))))`, exactly as your RenderDoc disassembly shows.

**Refined trigger (both conditions required):**

| Condition | Role |
|-----------|------|
| `saturate(dot(halfAngle, normal)) == 0` | `log2(0) → -∞` |
| `materialSpecularPower == 0` (exactly) | `0.0 × (-∞) → NaN` (IEEE 754 indeterminate form) |
| `exp2(NaN) → NaN` | Specular term NaN |
| `result.rgb = diffuseLit + allSpecular` | **NaN poisons the whole pixel** even when diffuse is valid |

**IEEE chain on D3D11 / `ps_4_0`:**

```
nh = saturate(dot(H,N)) = 0
t  = log2(nh) = -INF
t  = t * materialSpecularPower = 0 * (-INF) = NaN   ← only when power == 0
dot3SpecularIntensity = exp2(NaN) = NaN
```

If **`materialSpecularPower > 0`** (even `0.001`), then `power * (-INF) = -INF` and **`exp2(-INF) = 0`** — no NaN on back-facing pixels. So your matte-material hypothesis is **correct for the NaN path**, but it is **not** “NaN on the whole surface” — it is “NaN on every pixel where **H·N = 0** while power is 0,” and because specular NaN is **added** to diffuse, those pixels go fully black. On matte materials that can be most of the visible area.

**Challenge to framing:** Do not trust the source-level guard:

```311:314:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/.planning/phases/17-psrc-census-char-select-beachhead/evidence/plan-17-04x-psrc-source-dump.txt
	//light per-pixel specular -- (H.N)^power
	float dot3SpecularIntensity = 0;
	if (dot3LightIntensity >= 0)
		dot3SpecularIntensity = pow(saturate(dot(halfAngle_o, normal_o)), materialSpecularPower);
```

`dot3LightIntensity` is already `saturate(L·N)`, so **`>= 0` is always true**. The compiler removes the branch; your disassembly has **no branch** before `log`/`exp`. That guard never protected `H·N == 0`.

**Cheapest confirmation in RenderDoc (draw 1612):**  
Read **`SwgVertexConstants` @ b0**, first `float4` (**`packedRegister0` / `dot3LightDirection`**), **`.w` = `materialSpecularPower`**. Expect **`0.0`** on matte interior/NPC materials. If `.w > 0` at a NaN pixel, the trigger is something else (e.g. bad half-angle varyings) — but your asm implicating `packedRegister0.w` strongly points at **power = 0**.

---

## D3D9 vs D3D11 divergence (file:line)

### Same asset file, different GPU programs

| Path | What runs | Where |
|------|-----------|--------|
| **D3D9 (`gl05`)** | Prebuilt **`ps_2_0` bytecode** from `pixelShaderProgram.m_exe` | ```34:35:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_PixelShaderProgramData.cpp``` |
| **D3D11 (`gl11`)** | **`//hlsl` PSRC recompiled** via `D3DCompile` → **`ps_4_0`**, after `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite` (cbuffer wrap) + Plan 17-07 VS-mirror wrapper | ```75:75:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_PixelShaderProgramData.cpp```, ```1228:1276:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_PixelShaderProgramData.cpp```, ```810:967:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_PixelShaderProgramData.cpp``` |

So “same `a_specmap_pp_ps20.psh`” means **same HLSL source on disk**, not the same ISA. D3D9 never recompiles that source at runtime; D3D11 does, with stricter `log2`/`exp2` IEEE behavior than legacy **`ps_2_0`** bytecode.

### `materialSpecularPower` upload — same intent, one D3D11 asymmetry

**Material capture (both):** `material.getSpecularPower()` → stored per pass.

```486:486:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp
					pm.m_power    = material.getSpecularPower();
```

```619:619:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp
			m_material.material.Power      = material.getSpecularPower();
```

**D3D9 PS constant (no clamp):**

```864:864:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp
			Direct3d9_StateCache::setSpecularPower(m_material.material.Power);
```

```428:430:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_StateCache.h
inline void Direct3d9_StateCache::setSpecularPower(float power)
{
	ms_specularPower = power;
```

Fed into PS dot3 block as **`localDirection.w`**:

```577:577:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp
					lightData.dot3.localDirection.w = Direct3d9_StateCache::getSpecularPower(); // materialSpecularPower stored in localDirection.w
```

**D3D11 PS constant (raw `pm.m_power`, no clamp):**

```919:920:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp
							DirectX::XMFLOAT4 const c0(-localDir.x, -localDir.y, -localDir.z, pm.m_power);
							std::memcpy(staging.data() + PSCR_dot3LightDirection               * 16, &c0,                          sizeof(DirectX::XMFLOAT4));
```

Slot mapping:

```54:54:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_LegacyPSConstants.h
	constexpr int PSCR_dot3LightDirection               = 0;   // .xyz = object-local light dir, .w = materialSpecularPower
```

**D3D11 VS only (clamped — does not fix PS NaN):** Plan 17-09 GAP-5 clamps **vertex** specular power to 32 when `power <= 0`, but **PS still gets raw 0**:

```2392:2409:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp
void Direct3d11_StateCache::setSpecularPower(float power)
{
	// ...
	float const safe = (power > 0.0f && power < 1.0e6f) ? power : 32.0f;
	// ...
	Direct3d11_StateCacheNamespace::s_slot0Shadow.lightData[25].w = safe;
```

```773:773:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp
				Direct3d11_StateCache::setSpecularPower(pmPower.m_materialValid ? pmPower.m_power : 32.0f);
```

**Conclusion:** D3D9 and D3D11 both **can** feed **`materialSpecularPower = 0`** to the PS. The live divergence is **`ps_2_0` bytecode vs `ps_4_0` recompile + `pow` lowering**, not “D3D11 clamps power and D3D9 doesn’t.” On D3D9, **`pow(x, 0)` with matte materials likely yields 0** (legacy SM2 behavior), which matches “specular off”; on D3D11, **`pow(x, 0)` is 1 for `x > 0` and NaN for `x = 0`** — doubly wrong for matte.

**Interior/NPC vs exterior:** Plausible **if** those assets use **`specularPower == 0`** (matte walls, skin/cloth) **and** shaders in the `*_specmap_*` / `h_spec_pp` family. Exterior shiny materials with **power > 0** avoid the NaN path on back faces (`exp2(-∞) = 0`). That correlation is **material + shader family**, not “interior” as a separate renderer bug.

---

## Scope: how many shaders use this pattern?

From the char-select PSRC dump (**22 unique HLSL PS**), **7** contain the same specular idiom (`dot3SpecularIntensity = 0; if (dot3LightIntensity >= 0) pow(saturate(dot(halfAngle…))…)`):

| Shader |
|--------|
| `a_specmap_pp_ps20.psh` |
| `h_specmap_cbmp_ps20.psh` |
| `h_envmask_specmap_ps20.psh` |
| `h_color2_specmap_cbmp_ps20.psh` |
| `h_spec_pp_ps20.psh` |
| `h_color2_specmap_bump_ps20.psh` |
| `h_color2_specmap_bump_aniso_ps20.psh` |

That covers **armor (`a_*`)**, **human body (`h_*`)**, and **POB-style specmap** paths — aligned with interiors + NPCs + char-select.

`Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.cpp` has **no `pow`-specific rule** today; fixing only `a_specmap_pp` in one place would miss the other six unless you patch **pre-compile PSRC** globally.

Other hazards (`rsq` on zero-length `normalize`, `/` in attenuation) exist elsewhere (see VS handoff in `.planning/handoff/gap6-bump-arms-vs-lighting-nan.md`) but are **not** what your PS disassembly shows for event 1612 — **NORMAL / half-angle normalize completed before the NaN `log`**.

---

## Ranked minimal fixes (D3D9 parity)

### 1. **Recommended: fix the specular idiom in the recompile lane (all asset PSRC)**

Replace the dead `if (dot3LightIntensity >= 0)` block with something that matches **matte-off + no NaN**:

```hlsl
float nh = saturate(dot(halfAngle_o, normal_o));
dot3SpecularIntensity = (materialSpecularPower > 0.0f && nh > 0.0f)
    ? pow(nh, materialSpecularPower)
    : 0.0f;
```

**Where:** text substitution in `Direct3d11_PixelShaderProgramData.cpp` (before `D3DCompile`, alongside the Plan 17-07 wrapper) **or** a new rule in `Direct3d11_HlslRewrite.cpp`.  
**Why:** covers all 7 templates; **`power == 0 → 0`** matches D3D9 matte intent; **`nh == 0 → 0`** matches safe specular off back-faces; does not change **`power > 0`** exterior specular where `nh > 0`.  
**Verify:** bump `D3D11_REWRITE_VERSION`, one interior pixel → finite `o0`, diffuse visible.

### 2. **Do not: clamp `materialSpecularPower` to ≥ 1 at upload only**

Using `setSpecularPower`’s safe value in PS `c0.w` (line 919) would stop NaN but turn matte into **`pow(nh, 32)`** on lit pixels — **not** D3D9 matte (where **`pow(*, 0)` ≈ 0**). Worse than (1).

### 3. **Weaker: `pow(max(nh, 1e-8), max(power, 1e-8))`**

Avoids NaN but changes **all** specular falloff and **`power == 0`** semantics; poor D3D9 match.

### 4. **Post-hoc NaN sanitize on specular only**

e.g. `dot3SpecularIntensity = isnan(x) ? 0 : x` — stops black but leaves wrong **`pow(nh,0)==1`** on front-facing pixels; band-aid.

### 5. **Wrapper `isnan` on COLOR0/COLOR1** (already there)

```944:951:D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_PixelShaderProgramData.cpp
				// NaN GUARD: if a residual NaN slips through ...
				char arg[72]; _snprintf_s(arg, sizeof(arg), _TRUNCATE,
					"(any(isnan(i1707.f_%d)) ? 0 : i1707.f_%d)", paramToVs[k], paramToVs[k]);
```

Does **not** fix **internally generated** specular NaN (your finding #7).

